<p>GE.<footnote name="1">7. The delegation noted that the efforts of Gabon in the area of human rights policy did 
not place it above criticism or comment. However, criticism should be viewed as an 
invitation to improve, as human rights were an ideal. Gabon was working towards that ideal 
and assured the international community that it would continue to strive to reach it.  </footnote>2-18722  (E)    070113    080113 
